<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="416" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,258,823]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,402,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The embolic disc and embolus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[707,824,402,427]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[707,824,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[831,920,402,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,920,402,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[1179,1283,402,427]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis box="[1179,1283,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[1297,1429,403,427]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis box="[1297,1429,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galvis" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,333,438,463]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis box="[151,333,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. colombianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[405,554,439,462]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrigenu" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[405,554,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. nigrigenu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[569,667,438,463]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[569,667,438,463]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
: there are two dPED and the vPED is proximal and projects retrolaterally; also, the embolus is thicker and sickle-shaped. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[973,1092,474,499]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[973,1092,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1101,1193,474,499]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1101,1193,474,499]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from those species by the finger-shaped RvTA (
<figureCitation box="[706,795,510,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1889,1911]" captionTargetBox="[218,1360,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Amphidraus simplex sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, ventral view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; po, coupling pocket; PS, primary spermatHeca; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; SS, secondary spermatHeca; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855479/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Figs 14</figureCitation>
C, 14D), being slender and sinuous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[1244,1351,510,535]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis box="[1244,1351,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galvis" authorityYear="2017" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. colombianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, quadrangular with one tooth in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[660,793,547,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis box="[660,793,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Galiano" box="[851,1007,546,571]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" refString="Galiano, M. E. (1967) Dos nuevas especies del genero Amphidraus Simon, 1900 (Araneae, Salticidae). Physis Buenos Aires (C), 27, 95 - 100." type="journal article" year="1967">Galiano 1967</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 4), and rounded with two teeth in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,296,583,606]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrigenu" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,296,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. nigrigenu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[307,402,582,607]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[307,402,582,607]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[421,507,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1915,1937]" captionTargetBox="[206,1426,223,1874]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,193,1934]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Amphidraus nigrigenu sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855471/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
D). It also differs from all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[831,968,582,607]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[831,968,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Amphidraus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the presence of stout scales emerging from the proximal portion of the tibia (
<figureCitation box="[699,785,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1889,1911]" captionTargetBox="[218,1360,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Amphidraus simplex sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, ventral view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; po, coupling pocket; PS, primary spermatHeca; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; SS, secondary spermatHeca; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855479/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Figs 14</figureCitation>
B, 14D). The females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1063,1180,618,643]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1063,1180,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1187,1277,618,643]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1187,1277,618,643]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[1292,1374,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1889,1911]" captionTargetBox="[218,1360,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Amphidraus simplex sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, ventral view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; po, coupling pocket; PS, primary spermatHeca; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; SS, secondary spermatHeca; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855479/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
F), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[237,369,655,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis box="[237,369,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[384,464,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1801,1823]" captionTargetBox="[209,1317,203,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[196,1364,193,1753]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 16. MorpHological variations in copulatory structures of Amphidraus santanae. A, C, E, G, left male palp, ventral view. B, D, F, H, same, tibia, retrolateral view; A – B specimen from Vitória do Xingu, Pará; C – D specimen from São Félix do Xingu, Pará; E – F specimen from Canaã do Carajás, Pará; G – H specimen from Tailândia, Pará; I – L epigyne, cleared, ventral view; I female from Vitória do Xingu, Pará; J female from São Félix do Xingu, Pará; K female from Canaã do Carajás, Pará; L female from Tailândia, Pará. CD, copulatory duct; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; po, coupling pocket; PS, primary spermatHeca; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SS, secondary spermatHeca; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855485/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
Fig. 
<date box="[436,464,654,679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" value="2016-01">16</date>
</figureCitation>
I) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[536,642,654,679]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifidus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[536,642,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. bifidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[649,738,654,679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[649,738,654,679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[753,832,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1912,1934]" captionTargetBox="[220,1384,193,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1891]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 21. Amphidraus bifidus sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, dorsal view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; PS, primary spermatHeca; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; SS, secondary spermatHeca; TL, tegular lobe." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855505/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
F) have semicircular secondary spermathecae near the copulatory openings. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[528,651,690,715]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplex" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[528,651,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[666,762,690,715]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[666,762,690,715]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from all 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1900" box="[972,1109,690,715]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[972,1109,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Amphidraus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in having a single copulatory opening (atrium), whereas the other species have two copulatory openings. In addition, its coupling pocket is located ventrally in the middle portion of the epigynal plate (
<figureCitation box="[960,1046,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1889,1911]" captionTargetBox="[218,1360,194,1867]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,193,1867]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Amphidraus simplex sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, ventral view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; po, coupling pocket; PS, primary spermatHeca; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; SS, secondary spermatHeca; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855479/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Figs 14</figureCitation>
E, 14F), whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" box="[1248,1354,762,787]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duckei">
<emphasis box="[1248,1354,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. duckei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Galiano" authorityYear="1967" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">A. santanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have dorsal pockets on the posterior border of the epigynal plate (
<figureCitation box="[994,1079,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1839,1861]" captionTargetBox="[356,1249,660,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[356,1253,660,1808]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 15. MorpHological variations in copulatory structures of Amphidraus santanae. A – C, E – G, I – K, M – O: left male palp; A – C Holotype from Santana, Amapá; E – G specimen from Vitória do Xingu, Pará; I – K specimen from São Félix do Xingu, Pará; M – O specimen from Canaã do Carajás, Pará; A, E, I, M: ventral views; B, F, J, N: retrolateral views; C: proventral view; G, K, O: retroventral views. D, H, L, P: epigyne, ventral view; D allotype from Santana, Amapá; H female from Vitória do Xingu, Pará; L female from São Félix do Xingu, Pará; P female from Canaã dos Carajás, Pará. dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855483/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Figs 15</figureCitation>
D, 
<date box="[1113,1151,798,823]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" value="2016-01">16I</date>
–L).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
